<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,909,935]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is made after Dr. Wagner Magalhães in recognition of his careful study of polychaetes species, and for his friendship especially with one of the authors (AER). The epithet is a noun in the genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1016,1043]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McIntosh" authorityYear="1922" box="[327,470,1017,1043]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fauveliopsidae" genus="Fauveliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,470,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fauveliopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with long body, posteriorly swollen, divided into three different regions by integument and chaetation. Integument rugose, papillated anteriorly (ca. 10 first chaetigers), followed by a transitional less rugose papillated region, and a third region (posterior chaetigers) weakly papillated, almost smooth. First 3 chaetigers: aA/Aa, with safety-pin falcate (SPF) neurochaetae; chaetigers 4 to 16–25 (depending on body size): cA/Ac (except for replacement chaetae); ca. 10 last chaetigers with multiple neurochaetae: cA/1–3A1–3c. Ventral shield usually present, elongate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1232,1259]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[350,454,1233,1259]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Holotype</typeStatus>
(UERJ 1336) with long body, posteriorly swollen, divided into three different regions by integument and chaetal features (
<figureCitation box="[522,630,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1622,1647]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,185,1593]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[170,1418,181,1597]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 0.2 mm; B–C: 0.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335224/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 13A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[642,694,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1427,1452]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,183,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[170,1418,181,1401]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 14. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype.A (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, median region, dorsal view. D. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. E. Epithelial papillae. F. Last chaetigers and pygidium, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 330 µm, B, 140 μm, C: 150 μm, D: 200 μm, E: 20 μm, F: 110 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335226/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">14A</figureCitation>
). Anterior and median segments distinct, posterior ones indistinct. Whitish, without pigmentation (
<figureCitation box="[510,614,1305,1331]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1622,1647]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,185,1593]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[170,1418,181,1597]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 0.2 mm; B–C: 0.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335224/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Prostomium invaginated, fused to peristomium (
<figureCitation box="[742,845,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1622,1647]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,185,1593]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[170,1418,181,1597]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 0.2 mm; B–C: 0.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335224/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Peristomium marginating mouth. Mouth as a vertical incision, distal, with inverted T-shaped opening.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Integument opaque, very rugose, papillated along anterior region (first 10–12 chaetigers; 
<figureCitation box="[1225,1363,1413,1439]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1427,1452]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,183,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[170,1418,181,1401]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 14. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype.A (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, median region, dorsal view. D. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. E. Epithelial papillae. F. Last chaetigers and pygidium, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 330 µm, B, 140 μm, C: 150 μm, D: 200 μm, E: 20 μm, F: 110 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335226/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 14B, C</figureCitation>
), with about 15 rows of triangular papillae, followed by a less rugose, papillated transitional region, papillae slightly small- er than those present along anterior region (
<figureCitation box="[643,746,1485,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1427,1452]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,183,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[170,1418,181,1401]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 14. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype.A (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, median region, dorsal view. D. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. E. Epithelial papillae. F. Last chaetigers and pygidium, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 330 µm, B, 140 μm, C: 150 μm, D: 200 μm, E: 20 μm, F: 110 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335226/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
). Posterior region (last 10 chaetigers) rugose, almost smooth, except for a few minute papillae, transparent (
<figureCitation box="[665,769,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1427,1452]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,183,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[170,1418,181,1401]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 14. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype.A (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, median region, dorsal view. D. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. E. Epithelial papillae. F. Last chaetigers and pygidium, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 330 µm, B, 140 μm, C: 150 μm, D: 200 μm, E: 20 μm, F: 110 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335226/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
). Triangular papillae with a dorsal pore, arranged on rugose ridge (
<figureCitation box="[224,326,1557,1583]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1427,1452]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,183,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[170,1418,181,1401]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 14. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype.A (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, median region, dorsal view. D. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. E. Epithelial papillae. F. Last chaetigers and pygidium, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 330 µm, B, 140 μm, C: 150 μm, D: 200 μm, E: 20 μm, F: 110 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335226/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 14E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
First 10–12 segments sharply demarcated by tranverse sulci. Segments of median and posterior regions indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[216,316,1629,1655]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1427,1452]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,183,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[170,1418,181,1401]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 14. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype.A (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, median region, dorsal view. D. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. E. Epithelial papillae. F. Last chaetigers and pygidium, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 330 µm, B, 140 μm, C: 150 μm, D: 200 μm, E: 20 μm, F: 110 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335226/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 14F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Parapodia lateral, flat and little developed in anterior and posterior regions, even inconspicuous in median region. Interramal papilla pedunculate, tip granulated, located between notopodia and neuropodia along anterior region; smaller and closer to notopodia in median and posterior regions.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
In first segments chaetae directed anteriorly, following ones directed laterally or posteriorly. First 4 segments with aA/Aa, i.e. one capillary and one stouter and curved acicular; neurochaetae safety-pin falcate (SPF). From chaetiger 4 to 16–25 (depending of body size) noto- and neuropodia with one capillary and one acicular each on median chaetigers (cA/Ac). Last 10 chaetigers with multiple neurochaetae: usually cA/1–3A1–3c (
<figureCitation box="[1271,1374,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1622,1647]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,185,1593]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[170,1418,181,1597]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. Fauveliopsis magalhaesi n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 208). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Same, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, posterior region, dorsal view. Scale bars: A: 0.2 mm; B–C: 0.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335224/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
). Replacement chaetae can be present in noto- and neuropodia along body.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Genital papilla not seen. Pygidium inconspicuous, with minute papillae close to anal opening. Probably living in scaphopod shells.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
